# Esiana Engineering Guardrails

Source: [engineeringprinciples.md](../../engineeringprinciples.md), [tenant-isolation-audit.md](../../docs/security/tenant-isolation-audit.md).

## Database agnosticism

- No PostgreSQL-only or SQLite-only SQL, triggers, or engine-specific behavior
- Migrations and queries stay portable via Prisma abstractions

## Multi-tenant isolation

Campaigns are isolated tenants. No cross-campaign leakage in queries, caches, search, plugin data, or exports.

```typescript
// Good — scoped mutation
const page = await prisma.wikiPage.findFirst({ where: { id, campaignId } });
if (!page) return res.status(404).end();

// Bad — id-only update (cross-tenant risk)
await prisma.wikiPage.update({ where: { id } }, data);
```

Every campaign-scoped route: scope middleware + membership checks + `campaignId` in reads/writes.

## Data sovereignty

Prefer exportable formats (Markdown + frontmatter, portable ZIP backups). Avoid lock-in and opaque proprietary blobs for core lore.

## API-first

New core behavior exposes stable APIs. Frontend uses APIs — not privileged direct DB access when an equivalent API can exist.

## Plugins

Plugins are capability-constrained integrations, not unrestricted code execution. Core remains authoritative over permissions, provenance, temporal integrity, and tenant boundaries.
